		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2009"></a><br><code>sle2009/paper02</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2009</a> paper:</span><br><i>A Novel Approach to Semi-automated Evolution of DSML Model Transformation</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/TihamérLevendovszky.html">Tihamér Levendovszky</a>, <a href="../profile/DanielBalasubramanian.html">Daniel Balasubramanian</a>, <a href="../profile/AnanthaNarayanan.html">Anantha Narayanan</a>, <a href="../profile/GáborKarsai.html">Gábor Karsai</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-12107-4_4">10.1007/978-3-642-12107-4_4</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2b.html"><span class="tagM">T2B: Evolution</span></a><ul><li> The core contribution is a method for evolving model transformations as DSMLs and their artifacts change.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3b.html"><span class="tagL">T3B: Transformation Languages</span></a><ul><li> Model transformations are central artifacts, so the work sits in transformation-language practice.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> Evolution is operationalized via mappings/conversions between versions of models and transformations.
</li></ul></li></ul>
